DBGET get a table, record, or field from a Datascope database

RECORD = DBGET( DBPTR, [ 'dbSCRATCH' ] )

DBGET may be usee to get records, fields, or even an entire
table from a database. The requested information is
returned as RECORD, unless the second argument 'dbSCRATCH'
is given, in which case the requested information is put
into the scratch record for the corresponding table.
